    "name": "Grid Independence Study — Centrifugal Pump CFD Mesh Refinement",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted across four mesh densities (0.8 M, 2.1 M, 5.4 M, and 11.2 M elements) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. The study evaluated convergence of wall shear stress distributions and velocity profiles at the impeller outlet plane. Richardson extrapolation was applied to quantify the grid convergence index (GCI) for each quantity of interest. The 5.4 M element mesh was selected as the production mesh, exhibiting GCI values below 2% for all primary hemolysis-relevant quantities. This activity was completed prior to the validation simulations and its outputs informed the discretization error factor assessment.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
    "startedAtTime": "2025-09-10T08:00:00Z",
    "endedAtTime": "2025-09-18T17:00:00Z"
  },
