    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-hemolysis-validation-result-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD Hemolysis Prediction vs. Experimental Benchmark — 5 Operating Points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against experimental measurements at five flow-speed operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3.5 L/min at 3000 RPM, 5.0 L/min at 3500 RPM, 6.0 L/min at 3500 RPM, 7.0 L/min at 4000 RPM). Predicted RH values fell within ±18% of experimental values across all operating points. The worst-case operating condition (7.0 L/min, 4000 RPM) was correctly identified by the CFD model. Discretization error contributions, informed by the mesh refinement narrative documented in the credibility assessment, were accounted for in the uncertainty budget. All RH predictions remained below the acceptance threshold of RH < 1 relative to the predicate device.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cfd-validation-simulation-run-001"
